{
  "stem": "27509.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And at the age of 80, she wrote letters in Hebrew to relatives in Israel that amazed me then, because I, today-- and I-- my Hebrew was much deeper and much far-fetched.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I have to go to a dictionary today, to make sure the spelling of a word.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She didn't have to go to a dictionary, to such a degree.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was a religious also, in the sense, of course, that if she wouldn't have been religious, there would have been no match-- put it this way.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, my father wouldn't have contemplated marrying a woman who was not religious.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Her father, as I told you, was a Talmudic scholar also, but not of the same level of rabbinical excellence that our-- of father's family-- different level, but rabbis.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- but she was a much more modern person.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If she would have married another type of man, she would have most probably been a different type of a lady, with much-- she loved speaking.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She would, at the drop of a pin, make a speech, unprepared, unrehearsed, and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she loved it-- and fluent, and so on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Whatever the reason may be, [? most probably ?] [INAUDIBLE], credit to my mother, not my father.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My father was a man of few words, of very few words.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With my mother-- well, you know, mothers-- she was a mother of five children, and I was the oldest.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the oldest child, according to Jewish law, gets an extra portion of everything, even-- even of love.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and of course, I had-- I was looked on as somebody with some promise, although, as time moved on, my younger-- my other siblings were equally capable, by and large.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it was a very warm, a very warm mother.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
